cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.SD 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper describes the ARIEL-CMU submissions to the Low Resource Human Language Technologies (LoReHLT) 2018 evaluations for tasks related to natural language processing (NLP) such as Machine Translation (MT), Entity Discovery and Linking (EDL), and detection of Situation Frames in Text and Speech (SF Text and Speech).
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of machine learning techniques for the NLP tasks.
- cs.LG (Learning) is another possible category as the paper may involve the use of supervised and unsupervised learning methods for the NLP tasks.
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a possible category as the paper may involve techniques for retrieving relevant information from text and speech data.
- cs.SD (Sound) is a less likely category but still possible as the paper mentions the detection of Situation Frames in Speech.
